Job Description:
- Be responsible for:
• Manage assigned loan products (especially in Installment Product/Credit Card Sector), including but not limited to analyzing and keeping track of product performance, P&L and policy;
• Design end-to-end product process and procedures: Product proposal, Business Requirements Document, UAT Test, Production and related documents,…
• Improve the existing products in order to ensure the suitability and enhance its attractiveness to the market;
• Proposing new product/ new services / business cooperation models through research markets, competitors and understand customer needs in-depth .
• Keep track and adjust regularly the product regulations/ sales policies to ensure the compliance with Government, SBV and Company internal policies;
• Conduct market research and competitor studies to maintain competitiveness, identify opportunities, gaps and areas for improvement;
• Work closely related departments to solve daily issues and propose enhancement/improvement for sales/operation procedure/process/system
• Follow and continuously tracking the performance of existing products;
• Make related reports as required
• Other tasks assigned by Head of Department.

This position supports student services by helping implement student policies, coordinating required extra-curricular activities for graduation, assisting with bus services, and keeping student information on the ASA website up to date.

- Manage student bus service;
- Handle policy affairs for students (exemption of military service, tuition fee delay, tuition fee reduction, etc.); update students on new policies and regulations via different channels (email, posting on the VGU website, etc.);
- Advise students on university policies and procedures, ensuring awareness and compliance;
- Conduct training/info sessions/meetings/events to educate students and staff on relevant policies and procedures regarding student policies;
- Organize extra-curricular student activities required as conditions for granting degrees;
- Coordinate the process of issuing student ID cards to students;
- Coordinate, request and distribute VGU T-shirts to students, faculty, staff, alumni, and other members appropriately;
- Issue testimony certificates proving students' enrollment status (testimony, reference letter, enrolment certificate, late graduation, etc.);
- Stay current with relevant laws, regulations, and best practices in student affairs for student policy and support;
- Provide information on VGU services and procedures;
- Support student data management systems such as SLCM, SIS and HEMIS and provide student data statistics and analysis;
- Support enrolment procedures.

Sourcing, analyzing, monitoring real estate investment opportunities
Key Responsibilities
• Work closely with the Executive Officers and Directors to evaluate real estate investment opportunities and manage portfolio of real estate investments;
• Work closely with the Executive Officers and Directors to identify and coordinate with JV partners, buyers, and co-investors to facilitate the disposition of land, projects under development, and operating assets.
• Lead the due diligence process and coordinate with relevant team members including the PM, legal, and finance teams to cover physical, legal, and accounting issues;
• Investment experience through full life cycle of a project including site sourcing, acquisition, planning and development, construction, operations, and disposition.
• Collect and convert primary data into relevant format for review by Executive Officers and Directors, make research on additional and related information as required and be involved in the evaluation of prospective investment opportunities;
• Prepare Investment Memo to be presented to the Executive Officers and Directors to seek approval on any investment or disposal of assets;
• Manage, structure, execute real estate transactions;
• Perform financial analysis and recommendations for real estate transactions;
• Perform market analysis and due diligence on real estate projects and industry;
• Analyze investment opportunities by building financial models and quantitative analysis;
• Analyze deal structure and work closely with legal team in drafting transaction documents;
• Monitor the performance of investment portfolios;
• Manage project’s cash flow, capital financing and project’s budget;
• Write investment reports;
• Work with Vendors and third parties on real estate transactions;
• Others as assigned by Executive Officers and Directors.

